		<b>Comment By Jenny Shank, 9-29-05</b>
		<p>Hi Kyla,<br />
<br />
I'm glad the pikas have such a passionate advocate as you.  The solutions to save pikas aren't simple, as their endangerment has been caused by global warming, but the World Wildlife Fund has set up a special Pika fund that you can donate to:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.newwest.net/?URL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldwildlife.org%2Fpikas%2F">http://www.worldwildlife.org/pikas/</a><br />
<br />
There is a lot of good info on pikas on this webpage of a UC Davis research team, too:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.newwest.net/?URL=http%3A%2F%2Fice.ucdavis.edu%2Fpika%2Fpikapage.html">http://ice.ucdavis.edu/pika/pikapage.html</a><br />
<br />
Other than that, anything you can personally do to limit the creation of greenhouse gases--such as riding your bike instead of driving--will be the best way to help pikas.</p>
		
